<br>
I 2 box with cleric a lot and it was painful to loose that OOM to FM with rods in 20 secs while only using 40M of the cleric's mana, but those days are gone.<br>
<br>
I now 2 box on mobs that hit for 350 plus with 10 12k hp and my DD/rain rocks and my pets rock.  I ch heal only 2 times in a fight and cast our nice 2300 plus DD 2 times and DD click 250 dam the rest of the time on a horse. I time the last heal to go off about the time rage might go off and I can even handle 2 mobs on my pet at once but will use a lot of mana. <br>
<br>
I buff pet with cleric buffs (do not have aego yet) and give him all the armor/pet items I can.<br>
<br>
I was next to a shammy SK team and was killing mobs 2 to 3 per their one and my cleric stays around FM and I never go below 60m. I keep KEI on at all times.  <br>
<br>
I get 1/2 blue of AA per kill and can get a full AA point in 3 to 4 hours of play. This is by far better exp then when I had the old mod rods with cleric in FG or the gray zone for AA exp, so the single or partner exp blows the old exp out of the water, plus PoV exp in a full group is close to this too. It took me about 2 days of good exping to get a AA in the pre pop days. I now can get 3 or 4 a days if all I did was exp for that day. This is close to AOE group level exp without AOEing.<br>
<br>
I am once again respected as a Damage dealer, and with my mana pool and new line of spells I'm close to if not top damage dealer in my guild now where before druids at my level and wizards 5 levels below me before pop were able to out damage me easily.<br>
<br>
I grouped with a level 64 wizard and he couldn't believe the damage out put my DD/rain was doing, and then he stood next to Jaber and said my god your 60 level pet is out damaging the 62 level monk. <br>
<br>
I know my air pet can tank with all the buffs well on any mob that hits below 500 dam in pop and some times better then a warrior. Healers get zero argo from pet heals and once you get the timing right he can have the full heal go off when Jaber HP is in the last bubble. This is something you would never do on a warrior, so there is no waisted heals on a pet and you can use CH with zero chance of argo. BTW on 350-370 damage mobs I heal at 40% HP on pet and on 450 damage mobs I start heal at 60%. If the mobs get super great hits in where it looks like Jaber might die before heal goes off I step in and take a few seconds of damage to help. This works super. I'm not sure when normal clerics start their heals on Main tanks but it seems when I do group the are healing a lot more then my cleric is on my pet.<br>
<br>
With all this how can anyone say we suck.  I do wish they would tweak our AA PoP skills some to make them more effective, but over all I'm having a lot more fun and getting a lot more exp then the pre pop days.<br>
<br>
