align=absmiddle>  power of the rod</span><hr size=1> have you actually ever tested this because you sure seem to be talking out your ass, you can do FAR more damage at 60 with rods then you could do at 65 without rods. Its not even a close comparison, if you have a healer that is, and what mods meant to a raid was imeasureable. In no way in no uncertien terms are we anywhere close to as powerful as we were with rods. Anyone who has examined it under both conditions would even consider it close or debateable. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=h0gfather>H0gfather</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 756<br> <font color=#333333>(12/6/02 10:55:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=419.topic&index=10>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.aus-1.au.nu/images/photo.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: pre 60</span><hr size=1> My personal opinion is that the &quot;recent&quot; pet changes, Mod Rod nerf and attention to the Mage class is part of a single effort to manipulate the class. The series of enhancements prior to the Nerf were just too conveniently timed to be considered otherwise.<br>
<br>
If you look at the entirety of the changes to Mages, rather than focusing on a single element, then clearly every Magician regardless of level is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>well ahead</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> today then we were 6 months ago. <br>
<br>
I don't see the need for much more work to be honest. I would love to see some attention taken to irritating bugs like pets poofing on stairs etc, but every class has a nice bug list to push. <br>
<br>
I was disheartened at the extreme difficulty to solo into the 60s. However, getting 65 was a choice I made, fully knowing that I would lose the ability to solo. I considered it carefully, but decided that the benefits of the added power that comes with the new levels outweighed the dwindling supply of solo mobs.<br>
<br>
I'm not in an uber guild, actually I'm in no guild at all. Getting groups is rough, but the benefits are there. Part of committing to the post-60 game is sticking it out and getting to 65, even if you don't have any spells past 62. Sitting on Valor hill, with a range of 60+ people LFG, groups will grab the highest level person they can find.<br>
<br>
